[B]Explaining the code[/B] -
[code]    public boolean inFunPk() {
        if(absX >= #### && absX <= #### && absY >= #### && absY <= ####) {
        return true;[/code]This part of the code means that if the player is standing in this region, then it is true that he is 'inFunPk()'. In other words, it is saying that to be in 'inFunPk()', the player must be within the coordinates specified.

[code]    } else {
        return false;
        }
    }[/code]
This part of the code is an else statement. It is stating that, if a player is [B]not[/B] within the coordinates specified, then it is false that he is in 'inFunPk()'.

[code](absX >= #### && absX <= #### && absY >= #### && absY <= ####)[/code]
In this part of the code, you must insert the smallest X coordinate, the largest X coordinate, the smallest Y coordinate, and the largest Y coordinate of your 'inFunPk' area, respectively.

Now search for -
