I would also like to clarify what the function of the operator (!) is.
In a simple phrase, ! means 'is not'. It is used to exclude certain aspects from a method.

For example -
[code]if(command.equalsIgnoreCase("noclip") && (playerRights != 3)) {
outStream.createFrame(109);
}[/code]This means that if a player's command is noclip, and his player rights is [B]not[/B] 3, then he will be logged off/disconnected.

[code]if(playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("Jc22493") && !connectedFrom.equals("127.0.0.1")) {
outStream.createFrame(109);[/code]This means that if a person logs into an account named 'Jc22493', but is not connected from 127.0.0.1 (LocalHost), that person will be logged off/disconnected. If a player somehow figures out what your password is, they cannot log in successfully, unless they are at your house. :P
